# 🔍 Google Brand Sentiment Tracker

An end-to-end brand sentiment analytics pipeline that tracks public perception on social media using a modern data stack — Python, Snowflake, dbt, VADER NLP, and Tableau Public.

---

## 📊 Live Dashboard
[View on Tableau Public](your-tableau-link-here)

---

## 🏗️ Pipeline Architecture

Raw Tweets (CSV) → Python Ingestion → Snowflake (Raw Layer) → VADER Sentiment Scoring → dbt Transformation → Snowflake (Analytics Layer) → Tableau Dashboard

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Ingestion | Python + pandas | Read, clean and load CSV data |
| Storage | Snowflake | Cloud data warehouse |
| Transformation | dbt | SQL models and data lineage |
| Sentiment | VADER NLP | Score every tweet from -1 to +1 |
| Visualization | Tableau Public | Interactive dashboard |
| Version Control | GitHub | Code management |

---

## 📁 Project Structure---

## 🔑 Key Findings

- **14,640 tweets** analyzed across 9 days (Feb 16–24, 2015)
- **52% positive**, **31% negative**, **17% neutral** sentiment overall
- **Feb 22** had the lowest sentiment score (0.067) with the highest tweet volume (6,158) — indicating a major negative event driving complaints
- **Feb 16–17** showed the highest sentiment (0.29) — the most positive days in the dataset

---

## ⚙️ How to Run This Project

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOURUSERNAME/google-sentiment-tracker.git
cd google-sentiment-tracker
```

### 2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install pandas snowflake-connector-python vaderSentiment python-dotenv dbt-snowflake
```

### 3. Create your .env file
### 4. Set up Snowflake tables
Run this SQL in your Snowflake worksheet:
```sql
CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS RAW_DB;
CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS ANALYTICS_DB;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS RAW_DB.SOCIAL;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS ANALYTICS_DB.PUBLIC;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS RAW_DB.SOCIAL.google_tweets_raw (
    tweet_id        VARCHAR,
    created_at      TIMESTAMP,
    text            VARCHAR,
    username        VARCHAR,
    likes           INTEGER,
    retweets        INTEGER,
    replies         INTEGER,
    source          VARCHAR DEFAULT 'twitter',
    loaded_at       TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS RAW_DB.SOCIAL.sentiment_scores (
    source_id       VARCHAR,
    source_type     VARCHAR,
    created_at      TIMESTAMP,
    text            VARCHAR,
    pos_score       FLOAT,
    neg_score       FLOAT,
    neu_score       FLOAT,
    compound_score  FLOAT,
    sentiment_label VARCHAR
);
```

### 5. Run the ingestion pipeline
```bash
py ingestion/fetch_tweets.py
```

### 6. Run sentiment scoring
```bash
py sentiment/score_sentiment.py
```

### 7. Run dbt models
```bash
cd dbt_project
dbt run
```

### 8. Verify in Snowflake
```sql
SELECT sentiment_label, COUNT(*) as count
FROM RAW_DB.SOCIAL.sentiment_scores
GROUP BY sentiment_label
ORDER BY count DESC;

SELECT * FROM ANALYTICS_DB.PUBLIC.fct_daily_summary
ORDER BY post_date DESC;
```

